The numbers are placed on a hexagonal grid using axial coordinates  

\[
E=(1,0),\;NE=(0,1),\;NW=(-1,1),\;W=(-1,0),\;SW=(0,-1),\;SE=(1,-1)
\]

with \(1\) at \((0,0)\).  
For a given ring \(k\) the outermost (south‑east) corner has the number  

\[
N_{\max }(k)=1+3k(k+1)
\]

and its coordinates are \((k,-k)\).  
The six corner numbers of ring \(k\) are  

\[
\begin{aligned}
SE &: ( k,-k) \qquad  N_{\max }(k)\\
SW &: (0,-k) \qquad  N_{\max }(k)-k\\
W  &: (-k,0) \qquad  N_{\max }(k)-2k\\
NW &: (-k,k) \qquad  N_{\max }(k)-3k\\
NE &: (0, k) \qquad  N_{\max }(k)-4k\\
E  &: ( k,0) \qquad  N_{\max }(k)-5k
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### Locate 2026

\(2026\) lies in ring \(k=26\) because  

\[
N_{\max }(25)=1951<2026\le N_{\max }(26)=2107 .
\]

For \(k=26\) the corner numbers are  

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{corner}&\text{number}\\\hline
SE&(26,-26)&2107\\
SW&(0,-26)&2081\\
W&(-26,0)&2055\\
NW&(-26,26)&2029\\
NE&(0,26)&2003\\
E&(26,0)&1977
\end{array}
\]

Since \(2026\) is three steps east of the NW corner, its coordinates are  

\[
(-26+3,\,26)=(-23,26).
\]

---

### The six neighbours

Add the six direction vectors to \((-23,26)\) and convert each resulting coordinate back to its number.

| direction | coordinate | ring | number |
|-----------|------------|------|--------|
| East  \((+1,0)\) | \((-22,26)\) | 26 | \(2107-(78+4)=2025\) |
| West  \((-1,0)\) | \((-24,26)\) | 26 | \(2107-(78+2)=2027\) |
| North‑East \((0,+1)\) | \((-23,27)\) | 27 | \(2269-(81+4)=2184\) |
| North‑West \((-1,+1)\) | \((-24,27)\) | 27 | \(2269-(81+3)=2185\) |
| South‑West \((0,-1)\) | \((-23,25)\) | 25 | \(1951-(75+2)=1874\) |
| South‑East \((+1,-1)\) | \((-22,25)\) | 25 | \(1951-(75+3)=1873\) |

---

### Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
2025+2027+2184+2185+1874+1873
&= 4052+4369+3747\\
&= 8421+3747\\
&= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
